hackathon-description-text: HackFSU '15 is a hackathon where students will spend 30 hours collaborating and building incredible things.

hackathon-judges.judge-name: The Dopest Judges in the Area

hackathon-rules:
All hacks must be built during the 30 hours of hacking at HackFSU.
In addition to Major League Hacking's 
 we ask all attending HackFSU to adhere to the following:
1. 
 Hackathons can be super stressful, but you are the Ann Perkins to our Leslie Knope aka you are amazing and we love you, so have fun! We've worked really hard to provide you with a good work environment and we're happy to have you here!
2. 
 It goes a long way. Be kind to other hackers, mentors, sponsors, and the hackathon staff.
"Be kind to others. Do not insult or put down other attendees. Behave professionally. Remember that harassment and racist, sexist, or exclusionary jokes are not appropriate for this event*.
* Harassment includes offensive verbal comments related to gender, sexual orientation, disability, physical appearance, body size, race, religion, sexual images in public spaces, deliberate intimidation, stalking, following, harassing photography or recording, sustained disruption of talks or other events, inappropriate physical contact, and unwelcome sexual attention." - sourced from

hackathon-prizes.prize-content: Pebble watches and a Dell Bluetooth Speaker.
